    brief: "Investment responds to the rate of change in output, not its level, so rising demand triggers proportionally larger increases in capital spending.",
    more: "When output grows, firms must invest to expand capacity; when growth slows, even if output is still high, investment falls because existing capacity suffices. This makes investment highly volatile and amplifies business cycle fluctuations.",
