    detailed: "The functions of money are interdependent: only an asset that holds its value (store of value) will be accepted as payment (medium of exchange) and serve reliably as a unit of account. Hyperinflation destroys money by eroding the store of value function, as in Zimbabwe in the 2000s or the Weimar Republic in the 1920s, eventually causing the breakdown of the market economy. Cryptocurrencies aspire to the functions of money but currently exhibit high volatility that undermines the store of value and unit of account roles. Common mistake: Students treat money as identical to wealth. Money is a specific type of asset that serves transactional functions; wealth includes all assets, most of which are not money.",
